DataElement.preferredName: Clinical Study Site Protocol Identifier java.lang.Long
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of research study that tests how well new medical treatments or other interventions work in people.  Such studies test new methods of screening, prevention, diagnosis, or treatment of a disease.  The study may be carried out in a clinic or other medical facility.  Also called a clinical study._The buildings and organizations where healthcare services are provided._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._An action plan for a clinical trial.  The plan states what the study will do, how, and why.  It explains how many people will be in it, who is eligible to participate, what study agents or other interventions they will be given, what tests they will receive and how often, and what information will be gathered._A healthcare organization, a facility, a healthcare provider, or a part or a constituent of any of the above entities directly involved in conducting a particular clinical study._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
